The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 September is 73,217 (8,438.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 September, there were 1,565 new confirmed cases (180.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 September, there were 2,162 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 28% (597 fewer cases).
